    <p>As you can see, the primary ingredient in Smirnoff Ice Red White and Berry is malted barley, which is a source of gluten. This means that the beverage is not gluten-free. Additionally, the natural flavors used in the drink may also contain gluten, further increasing the risk for those with gluten sensitivity.</p>

    <h2>Is There a Gluten-Free Alternative?</h2>

    <p>If you’re looking for a gluten-free alternative to Smirnoff Ice Red White and Berry, there are several options available. Many brands offer gluten-free malt beverages or hard seltzers that are made with gluten-free grains like sorghum or rice. Some popular gluten-free alternatives include:</p>

