        <li><strong>Omission Beer:</strong> A gluten-free beer made with gluten-free grains and crafted to remove gluten.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>FAQs About Smirnoff Ice Red White and Berry</h2>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>1. Is Smirnoff Ice Red White and Berry safe for people with celiac disease?</h3>
        <p>No, Smirnoff Ice Red White and Berry is not safe for people with celiac disease as it contains malted barley, which is a source of gluten.</p>

        <h3>2. Can I drink Smirnoff Ice Red White and Berry if I have gluten sensitivity?</h3>
        <p>It’s not recommended. Even if you have a mild gluten sensitivity, consuming products with gluten can still cause discomfort and other symptoms.</p>

        <h3>3. Are there any gluten-free Smirnoff products?</h3>
        <p>Yes, Smirnoff offers some gluten-free products, such as their Smirnoff Vodka, which is made from corn and is considered gluten-free. However, always check the label to be sure.</p>

        <h3>4. What should I look for on the label to determine if a product is gluten-free?</h3>
        <p>Look for labels that explicitly state “gluten-free.” Additionally, check the ingredients list for any gluten-containing grains like wheat, barley, or rye.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>

    <p>In conclusion, Smirnoff Ice Red White and Berry is not gluten-free due to its primary ingredient, malted barley. For those with celiac disease or gluten sensitivity, it’s important to avoid this beverage and opt for gluten-free alternatives. Always read labels carefully and consult with a healthcare professional if you’re unsure about a product’s gluten content. By making informed choices, you can enjoy your favorite drinks without compromising your health.</p>

